Here is a simple function in Python that takes a list of strings as input and returns them combined into one string:

```python
def combine_strings(lst):
    return ''.join(lst)
```

This function uses the `''.join()` method to join all elements of the list (which must be iterable over characters). The result will be a single string with all the individual strings concatenated together.

